conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lord William Cramlington was born in 1377, in Preston, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard de Cramlington, was 61 and his mother, Eleanor De Kibblesworth, was 41. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. William Cramlington. He died in 1406, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 29."},"et":{"1377–1406":"1377–1406","1357–Male":"1357–Surnud","1378–Female":"1378–Surnud","1407–1466":"1407–1466","1316–1385":"1316–1385","1337–Female":"1337–Surnud","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1357":"1357","1466":"1466","1378":"1378","1377":"1377","1385":"1385","about 1355":"umbes 1355","1407":"1407","1406":"1406","Cramlington, Northumberland, England":"Cramlington, Northumberland, England","Preston, , Northumberland, England":"Preston, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Preston, Ellingham, Northumberland, England":"Preston, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1377–1406":"1377–1406","1357–Male":"1357–Kuollut","1378–Female":"1378–Kuollut","1407–1466":"1407–1466","1316–1385":"1316–1385","1337–Female":"1337–Kuollut","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1357":"1357","1466":"1466","1378":"1378","1377":"1377","1385":"1385","about 1355":"noin 1355","1407":"1407","1406":"1406","Cramlington, Northumberland, England":"Cramlington, Northumberland, England","Preston, , Northumberland, England":"Preston, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Preston, Ellingham, Northumberland, England":"Preston, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1377–1406":"1377–1406","1357–Male":"1357–Décédé","1378–Female":"1378–Décédée","1407–